 👨‍💻 DEVELOPER: TECHNICAL IMPLEMENTATION
 --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
 1. HOOK: useConsolidatedOrders
    - Parameter 'splitByFlow': 
      - FALSE (Default): Consolidates all orders into one card (Bar/Kitchen/Bills).
      - TRUE (Cashier): Splits Group vs Individual into different lanes.
 
 2. GROUPING LOGIC (The groupKey)
    - Base Key: Derived from table merging (e.g. "9-10" or "5").
    - Individual Lane Key: `${groupKeyBase}-indiv`
      - Purpose: Consolidates all staff-orders/extras into one card on that table.
      - Result: Table 9-10 merged in staff-order show as one "9-10" card.
    - Group Lane Key: `${groupKeyBase}-group-${reservation_id}`
      - Purpose: Isolates the group booking from any individual extras.
 
 3. UI MASKING
    - Friendly Name: Always use order.tableName or selectedTable.name.
    - Technical ID Scrubbing: 
      - (string).split('-')[0].replace(/^Bàn\s+/i, '')
      - Removes session-aware suffixes (-indiv, -group) for the user.
      - Result: "5-indiv-609" -> Displays as "5".
    - Lane Titles: Dashboard cards now exclude Company/Organization names 
      to favor pure table numbers (e.g. "Bàn 7-8-9").
    - Display Components: ActiveOrderTableList and similar grid components 
      automatically strip the "Bàn" prefix for a cleaner UI (e.g. "5").
    - Table Selector Visibility: The .select-tables row is now ONLY visible for 
      merged orders. For single individual tables, this section is hidden.
    - Interactive Labels: Buttons within the merged selector now display pure 
      numeric IDs (e.g. "3", "4") for a cleaner and more compact interface.
    - Dish List Headers: Group Reservation headers are also stripped of 
      technical tags (e.g. "group-53") and prefixes, displaying only the 
      numeric table range (e.g. "7 - 8 - 9").
 
 4. DATA INTEGRITY
    - Dictionary (orderDict): Populated during consolidation to ensure components 
      always find the correct session regardless of the split lanes.
    - multi-order support: table.active_orders (plural) is prioritized over active_order.